The paper discusses the use of side-channel information to reverse engineer a neural network, which falls under the category of security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on machine learning architectures (cs.LG) and discusses practical results on a microcontroller (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper deals with system-level attacks (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT) in terms of discussing mitigations for such attacks.
